        <h2 id="migration">5-step migration guide — Jasper to your new tool</h2>
        <p>If you decide to switch, here is the playbook we used with 8 teams over the last six months. Plan one working day end to end.</p>

        <div class="migration-steps">
          <div class="migration-step">
            <div>
              <span class="time">15 min</span>
              <h4>Export your Jasper documents and brand voice</h4>
              <p>From Jasper, open Workspace → Export. You will get a ZIP with documents and your brand-voice JSON. Save it locally — you will need the brand description text for your new tool.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="migration-step">
            <div>
              <span class="time">10 min</span>
              <h4>Inventory your top 50 ranking pages</h4>
              <p>Open Plausible or Search Console and sort by clicks over a 90-day window. Flag pages that need refreshes — these go first in your new tool.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="migration-step">
            <div>
              <span class="time">20 min</span>
              <h4>Upload brand voice to the new tool</h4>
              <p>theStacc, Writesonic, and Anyword all accept brand voice via URL or pasted text. Drop in your 3 best-performing posts and let the engine learn — usually faster than Jasper's manual style training.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="migration-step">
            <div>
              <span class="time">90 min</span>
              <h4>Recreate your 5 most-used templates</h4>
              <p>Most "templates" are saved prompts. 80% of teams use only 5 regularly. Save them in your new tool's prompt library and skip the long tail — you will not miss the rest.</p>
